<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-16T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/13a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WCS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-16T23:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Have received answers from the German Emperor, Austrian Emperor, King of
                            Great Britain and President of France to President’s, offer mediation.
                            Your message reported answer given by Foreign Office but stated that the
                            Czar was out of the city. Do you know if the President’s message has
                            been delivered to him? You might discreetly ask whether any further
                            answer is to be expected.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>